commentary: Holder to Azhar Ali, OUT has perished in his quest to up the scoring rate. Looks to go over mid-off but was completely deceived by the slower one that cut back in to beat his swing and hit the stumps. He was looking away towards midwicket when the wild bat swing missed the line of the ball, clearly no position to be in, but that can be discussed later. He walks off to a round of applause from the sparse crowd and his team-mates. This has been a determined knock at a time when he really needed it

commentary: Sohail Khan to Lewis, no run Sohail strikes on return! Given out. Lewis and Kraigg have a chat. WI opt for a review. Good length on middle, he plays around the front pad. Struck on the knee-roll of the front pad as Lewis is pinned on the crease. Did it pitch in line, though? HawkEye shows that it pitched marginally outside leg. First decision that has been overturned out of seven in this series

commentary: Sohail Khan to Lewis, 1 leg bye shuffles across off, plays around the front pad again. Not given, and Pakistan review now. This is tighter. It pitched marginally outside leg again, says the tracker. Phew!

This good length ball swings in, having started from outside leg, from over the wicket, and takes the leg stump. You don't need the umpires and the tracker for this. Many would have looked to play it straight or towards mid-on. Lewis was aiming for midwicket

commentary: Wahab Riaz to Bravo, OUT the struggle is finally over for Darren Bravo, and it's the extra pace that's done him in here. Bravo, perhaps expecting a short ball, was camping back. This one was floated at length around off. The ball fizzed through after pitching and a tentative poke away from the body found the edge as Sarfaz accepted it gleefully.

commentary: Wahab Riaz to Ramdin, OUT Oh, dear. What a terrible, terrible way to be dismissed. Ramdin chopped this to point and took a couple of paces down the pitch before turning his back on his partner. By then, Samuels had run almost the entire length of the pitch. Rizwan, who picked the ball up had the awareness to run towards the stumps and take the bails off rather than fire a throw. West Indies are crashing and burning here in the desert

commentary: Mohammad Nawaz to Narine, OUT steps out to flick but is beaten by one that skids straight on. Sarfraz effects the simplest of stumpings. Didn't make any effort to get to the pitch of the ball, neither did he try to get back into the crease once he was beaten. Too easy for Pakistan at the moment.

commentary: Wahab Riaz to Joseph, OUT 100 ODI wickets for Wahab! That would have got most tailenders. Bangs one in short from around the stumps, too quick for Joseph as he looks to pull, the bat face turns skywards as the top edge is taken easily by Shoaib Malik, who didn't have to move an inch at short midwicket. The end is near

commentary: Wahab Riaz to Ramdin, OUT that's the end of that. Gets a thick inside edge to square leg. No sooner than it hit the bat, Ramdin was off for the single without looking at his partner. Hassan Ali, who initially wanted to run to the stumps, lobbed the throw to Rizwan, who was backing up from point. He then ran to the stumps to whip the bails off with Ramdin nowhere in sight after being sent back
